Project Overview

This project is a console-based billing calculator developed in Python.
It allows users to perform basic billing operations through a menu-driven interface.
The application continuously interacts with the user, updates the total bill dynamically, and provides an easy way to simulate real-world billing systems.

Features

Menu-driven user interface
Add item cost to total bill
Apply discount to total bill
Multiply total amount (for quantity calculation)
Divide total amount (for splitting bill)
View updated total bill anytime
Continuous execution using loops
Exit option to terminate program

Problem Statement
Design and implement a menu-driven billing calculator that allows users to perform arithmetic operations and manage a total bill amount efficiently.

Objective
Perform basic billing calculations
Implement menu-driven programming
Understand input/output operations
Apply loops and conditional statements

Tools Used
Python 3
VS Code / IDLE

Description
This project simulates a simple billing system where the user can:

Add item costs
Apply discounts
Perform multiplication/division operations
Check total bill
The total bill updates after every operation.

Algorithm
Initialize total bill = 0
Display menu
Take user input
Perform selected operation
Update and display total
Repeat until exit

Conclusion
This project demonstrates the use of Python fundamentals like loops, conditions, and operators to build a simple real-world application.

